<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Islington</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well last weekend we advanced two of our Clerics to the Ragefire stage of the Cleric Epic.  Nagafen usually goes down right after patches on Erollisi Marr and we were counting on that.  After the 2nd patch on the 31, Phoenix Crusaders moved a group into the lair  to work on the Fire Giants and hold the camp.  In the meantime, every single person in the guild was on "Ragefire" watch.  Phone numbers were given out, resist gear backpacked etc.<P>Less than 24 hours after Naggy died, Ragefire popped for us.  It was totally amazing as 30 guildmates came together in roughly 5 minutes and began flooding Sol B.  I think that the camp was contested very briefly by one of the larger guilds on the server (for some reason they had an Ogre blocking the entrance to Sol B).  However the rest of their guild was apparently busy in ToV and eventually stood down.  I have no idea what happened but I personally believe it was just one person who got caught up in the heat of the moment and eventually realized that he alone could not do anything except trash a rep.  From what it appears, he was the only person who even MIGHT have been trying to contest the Ragefire.  Other than him we had no problems with other people or guilds.  After that we were left alone to kill Ragefire in our time.<P>Anyway, about half an hour of the first Ragefire sighting, we engaged.  The fight was over before we knew it and only lost a single member.<P>It was a neat experience and we now have our first Clicker in the guild.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Quistil Angelwatch<BR>Cleric of 41 Seasons in the service to the Great Mother Tunare<BR>Islington Angelwatch (Semi Retired)<BR>Paladin of 53 Seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr<BR>Phoenix Crusaders</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Eachann</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">congratulations!  I'm glad it went so well for you.  I sure hope things go as well for me when it's my turn (should that day ever come).   I still don't know how I'll camp ragefire, but it's good to know it was fun for somebody  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P><P>------------------<BR>Eachann Bronzeleaf<BR>Templar of Tunare, <BR>Tarew Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Walterscott</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Grats Islington!<P>I'd be curious what uber guild was giving you grief.  From most of what I've seen on our server (Emarr), it's a fairly decently respected camp.  If you are camping him first you get the first shot.<P>- Walt</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Islington</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>I'd be curious what uber guild was giving you grief.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Not going to say.  I really have no idea what was going on but anyone who was in the area would tell you that it looked VERY suspicious with an Ogre sitting directly in front of the entrance to Sol B in Lavastorm totally blocking the entrance.  I personally feel that it was a single individual who got caught up in the moment of having a Ragefire pop.  Besides in the end, he stood down and we went ahead and got our Ragefire.<P>In the end Dysan is one very happy Cleric.  Now we just need to get one more for Pyrde  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Had the stinking camp for 80 hours between the first Ragefire and the Patch.  Oh that ticked us off.  80 hours down the drain all due to Verant's patch... <P>------------------<BR>Quistil Angelwatch<BR>Cleric of 43 Seasons in the service to the Great Mother Tunare<BR>Islington Angelwatch (Semi Retired)<BR>Paladin of 53 Seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr<BR>Phoenix Crusaders</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gryfalia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, perhaps he left because it is virtually impossible for one person <BR>to block access to SolB.  For a good reason..<P>Zone into Sol A, down the stairs, through the first room and turn<BR>right.  Head down the ramp and after walking a tad you will<BR>find yourself zoning in SolB.  You can also do it through the<BR>goblin castle and 1-2 other places. <P>Perhaps he was actually smart enough to not want to be held<BR>up to server derision for being stupid..;-)<P>Gryfalia<BR>52 Vicar of Brell<BR>Imperial Guards<BR>Druzzil Ro<P>PS - camped Ragefire from Thursday night until he<BR>popped at 2PM CDT on Saturday for a guild cleric.  First<BR>time our guild has done this camp.  At least there are other<BR>things to DO in SolB, but they are all far away (but did pick<BR>up some Golden Efreeti Boots and a Polished Mithril Mask<BR>for my troubles).  Congrats Peppa Caliente on your Rez stick!<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Avenea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Or you could try jumping over him :P</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
